args:
The prince is concerned about New Alberia,
so Zena and Cleo use the power of the jewel to
return him to the Halidom. There, he reunites
with Patia and Leif, and informs his comrades
that he can return to the castle at any time
by making use of the jewel's power.
The Gran Fiore arrives in North Grastaea and\ndrops anchor while performing maintenance.\nMeanwhile, within the ship...
Hey, what's up, {player_name}?\nYou're looking a little glum.
I'm all right, Luca. I'm just thinking about\nhow everyone's doing back at the Halidom.
We left them in such a hurry,\nI hope they're all right.
And Dyrenell still has some forces at\ntheir disposal, so I'm worried about\nthe general citizenry as well.
Yeah, we did bug outta there pretty quick.\nAnd now that we're in North Grastaea,\nwe won't be heading back for a while.
If you're that worried, why don't we return\nto the Halidom and check in on them?
We certainly have the time; the ship will\nbe anchored here for quite a while.
I actually forgot to mention a few things\nregarding housekeeping around the castle\nmyself, so a trip back would not go amiss.
You both heard that, huh.\n...Wait, did you say we can go back?
YOU two might be into hoofing it all the\nway back there, but count ol' Luca out!
Oh, we have a much better idea in mind.\nBoth of you gather around Zena, please.
Er, okay. Is this close enough?
How fares the situation in the area\naround the Halidom, Patia?
Er, and I hope this isn't overstepping, sir,\nbut don't you think it would be best for us\nto follow the prince north?
No. Right now, our task is to remain here\nand safeguard both the Halidom and\nNew Alberia in his absence.
Though we may have Prince Leonidas,\nValkaheim is some distance from here.
And you want us to be ready to act in\nthe event something untoward occurs?\nYes, I suppose that makes sense.
Correct. Things are calm for the moment,\nbut there's no guarantee there will be no\nfurther rebellion against the royal family.

There are also a number of things which
tugged at my curiosity regarding the
citizen uprising that occurred while we
were making our way to New Alberia.

It was almost as though our path was
intentionally being blocked. Supposedly,
it was a faction of the Church that started
the ordeal...

Ostensibly, yes. Still, it's baffling that a
group that was such a minority within the
Church could have so quickly gained in
influence.
And yet, I am also worried that we've\nheard not a whisper of HIS activities\nsince the Empire fell.
You speak of Harle, I assume.\n...Wait, do you think HE is somehow\nbehind all the recent unrest?!
Without any concrete proof, it would be\npremature to make such a determination.

But in any case, he is a man one struggles
to read, and the possibility exists that he
may use the prince's absence as a chance
to sow great mischief.
When you look at it that way, we ought\nto keep our guard raised even whilst\nwe sleep.
Well, the prince and his companions\nshould have arrived in North Grastaea\nby now. I pray Ilia watches over them.
Hmm? This light... No!\nPatia, ready yourself!
It would appear we have arrived safely.\nWell done, Zena.
Wait, are we in the Halidom?!
This must be trickery or an illusion of sorts,\nyet my hand does not pass through him...
Please do not paw at our regent, Patia.
Leif! Patia! Why are you here?
We have been patrolling to ensure that\nnothing untoward happens at the Halidom\nin your absence.
I merely do my duty as a knight, Highness.
I was unable to make my way to the\nHalidom during your most recent crisis,\nand my own inadequacy shames me.
I heard about that from Leonidas.\nHe said you calmed the rebellion down\nin several key areas.
I'm grateful for your steadfast aid\nbehind the scenes.
Okay, this is all well and good, but can\nwe please get back to the part where we\nall got ZAPPED BACK TO THE HALIDOM?!
I mean, how is this even possible?
...So Alberius left a jewel to guide us\nto the Halidom, did he?
Yes, which means we can return\nhere any time we like.
Also, after consulting with Zena, we set up\nanother jewel on the deck of the landship.
Meaning we can get back to the\nGran Fiore from the Halidom.
So we can zap between the two\nas much as we want? Awesome!
Why didn't you tell us about this sooner?
We weren't trying to keep it a secret—\nwe merely wanted to perform some tests\nto ensure we could travel without issue.
And as we now have a strong command\nof the jewel, we figured it was time to\ninform everyone.
And with that, I have some business\nI must attend to. Farewell!
Then I suppose it's time for us to head\nback to the Gran Fiore.
I pray your journey bears fruit in the\ndays and weeks to come.
I firmly believe you will be equal and\nmore to any challenges which may\ncome before you in the future.
But do not hesitate if you have need of our\naid; we shall fly to your side at the first\nindication of trouble.
The Sparrows always have your back!
Thank you, both of you. I owe you more\nthan I can put into words.
Now let us be off, Brother.
Right. We'll see you again soon, guys.
Okay, I will NEVER get used to that!
It really is amazing; I can't thank the\ntwo of you enough for all your work.
It is King Alberius to whom we must be\ngrateful; all we did was find his jewel.
I'm certain that it is he who guides\nand watches over us even now.
Anyway, let's hurry and inform the others\nabout all of this.
The journey will be easier for everyone\nknowing we can return to the Halidom\nwhenever we need to.
